{
  "texts": [
    "With WordGame+, the maximum Attack Success Rate (ASR) is consistently over 90%, indicating that not only are WordGame and WordGame+ superior to existing attacks, they are also truly threatening to all LLM-based applications.",
    "Even when only a maximum of five attempts are allowed, WordGame and WordGame+ still receive considerable if not even more significant improvement over existing attacks as is shown in Table 1.",
    "The achievable ASR of WordGame is close to those in Table 2 when attacking the more dated but also more popular model like GPT 3.5, and WordGame+ sees even smaller performance loss due to limited queries.",
    "To fully leash the power of the proposed WordGame attack, we relax the query budget to 25 and use the more advanced GPT 4 as the attacker.",
    "The jailbreaking performances are reported in Table 2."
  ]
}